This code will break for non-ASCII header names or values:

```py
    def _decode_content(c):

        if _PY3:
            headers = Headers({
                key.decode('ascii'): [y.decode('ascii') for y in val]
                for key, val in response.headers.getAllRawHeaders()})
        else:
            headers = response.headers

        e = _encoding_from_headers(headers)
```

I don't think that this is necessary any more since Headers is Unicode-aware since Twisted 16.0.0 (https://github.com/twisted/twisted/commit/a1f64685abefed887af611455a5436d7a6fa0dc4).

There is an unmerged branch here:

